=== END CONTEXT ===


Wire every frontend page to its backend API. Use EXACT paths from PROJECT_API_ROUTES.md.

REQUIREMENTS:
1. Use TanStack Query (useQuery for reads, useMutation for writes)
2. Every API call has loading + error + empty states
3. Axios instance with interceptors for auth tokens (httpOnly cookies)
4. Interceptor has `_isRetry` flag to prevent infinite refresh loops (RULE-I1)
5. Never `setTimeout(() => navigate(...))` after API response (RULE-I2)
6. API paths must match @Controller decorators exactly (RULE-I3)
7. CORS origin + Playwright baseURL + Vite port must be consistent (RULE-I4)
8. No `any` types in response DTOs
9. Error messages use server response, not hardcoded strings

FILE LAYOUT:
- Use whichever source layout the project already uses: prefer frontend/app/
  (RR7 framework mode, what scaffold-frontend-shell produces) when it exists;
  fall back to frontend/src/ (legacy Vite/CRA) otherwise. Run
  `ls frontend/app/pages 2>/dev/null && echo app || echo src` to detect.
- <SRC>/services/api/*.ts (axios instance + per-resource services)
- <SRC>/hooks/api/use{Resource}.ts (TanStack Query hooks)
- Replace mock data in pages with real hook calls
- Do NOT create files under both src/ and app/ — duplicating breaks
  verify-page-coverage and the typecheck cascade (v25 evidence).

COVERAGE TARGET: wire >= 50% of pages on first pass. Prioritize:
  - All list pages (anything ending in List.tsx, ShowAll.tsx, or with a table)
  - All dashboards (Home.tsx, Dashboard.tsx)
  - All form pages (Apply.tsx, Create.tsx, Edit.tsx)
  - Auth pages
Pages without an obvious matching hook: leave them untouched but log them
under "## Skipped (no matching hook)" in the report — those are signals
that the backend is missing an endpoint and will self-heal next generation.

REPORT FILE: .claude-project/nestfind/status/INTEGRATION_REPORT.md
Required fields (regex-verifiable):
  phase: integrate
  endpoints_wired: <int>
  services_created: <int>
  hooks_created: <int>
  pages_updated: <int>
  pages_total: <int>
  pages_with_hooks: <int>
  coverage_pct: <int>
  rule_i1_interceptor_retry_flag: (true|false)
  rule_i3_route_matching: (true|false)

## Skipped (no matching hook)
  - <page-path>: <reason / which endpoint is missing>
  - ...

=== SECOND MANDATORY ARTIFACT: MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml ===

You MUST also write .claude-project/nestfind/status/MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml
— a STRUCTURED, machine-readable list of the backend endpoints that would
have let you wire the skipped pages. The next generation's backend phase
reads this file and generates those controllers automatically (self-heal
across generations).

If every page was wired, write the file with an empty missing_endpoints list.

Schema (emit in this exact shape — keys are parsed by the orchestrator):

```yaml
generated_at: <ISO timestamp>
gen: <integer, read from PIPELINE_STATUS.md `generation:` field; default 1>
total_pages: <int>
wired_pages: <int>
skipped_pages: <int>
missing_endpoints:
  - resource: notices              # kebab-case, used as NestJS module name
    module_name: notices           # matches backend/src/modules/{module_name}
    reason: <1-line why>
    suggested_routes:
      - method: GET
        path: /notices
        description: List notices for the current worker
        scope: worker              # one of: public | worker | company | admin
        response_shape: { items: NoticeDto[] }
      - method: GET
        path: /notices/:id
        description: Notice detail
        scope: worker
        response_shape: NoticeDto
      - method: POST
        path: /admin/notices
        description: Create notice (admin)
        scope: admin
        request_shape: CreateNoticeDto
        response_shape: NoticeDto
    consuming_pages:
      # Use whichever layout exists: app/pages (RR7) or src/pages (Vite).
      - frontend/<SRC>/pages/worker/Notices.tsx
      - frontend/<SRC>/pages/worker/NoticeDetail.tsx
      - frontend/<SRC>/pages/admin/Notices.tsx
      - frontend/<SRC>/pages/admin/NoticeCreate.tsx
  - resource: faq
    ...
```

GROUP by `resource` — one entry per missing backend module, not one per page.
Infer the `resource` name from the unwired page filenames (Notices.tsx → notices).
Suggest routes conservatively: GET /resource, GET /resource/:id, POST /resource,
PATCH /resource/:id, DELETE /resource/:id (only the subset the page actually needs).



